HEADWORD: Mycomelic
<hw>My`co*mel"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. (spurious)
<grk>my^kos</grk> mucus (L. <ets>mucus</ets>) + <grk>me`li</grk>
honey.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, a
complex nitrogenous acid of the alloxan group, obtained as a
honey-yellow powder. Its solutions have a gelatinous
consistency.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mycoprotein</ent>⟦br⟧
